    {
      "Channel": {
        "name": "arch-AnalyticsFlow",
        "channelID": "ch-aflw-ab1234"
      },
      "Message": {
        "User": {
          "userId": "eid_a3b1799d",
          "timestamp": "2026-03-15T14:10:00",
          "text": "Hey everyone, I've published the <https://sf-internal.slack.com/archives/docs/aflw_technical_architecture_document|Technical Architecture Document> for AnalyticsFlow. Please review and share your thoughts! 🚀",
          "utterranceID": "20260315-0-bbb01"
        },
        "Reactions": []
      },
      "ThreadReplies": [],
      "id": "20260315-0-bbb01"
    },
    {
      "Channel": {
        "name": "arch-AnalyticsFlow",
        "channelID": "ch-aflw-ab1234"
      },
      "Message": {
        "User": {
          "userId": "eid_46685257",
          "timestamp": "2026-03-15T14:12:00",
          "text": "Great document! I think we should add more detail about the data pipeline latency requirements in Section 3. The current benchmarks don't capture peak load scenarios.",
          "utterranceID": "20260315-1-bbb02"
        },
        "Reactions": []
      },
      "ThreadReplies": [],
      "id": "20260315-1-bbb02"
    },
    {
      "Channel": {
        "name": "arch-AnalyticsFlow",
        "channelID": "ch-aflw-ab1234"
      },
      "Message": {
        "User": {
          "userId": "eid_392456de",
          "timestamp": "2026-03-15T14:15:00",
          "text": "Solid architecture overview. One concern: the caching layer design might cause stale reads if we don't implement proper invalidation. I'd suggest adding TTL-based eviction.",
          "utterranceID": "20260315-2-bbb03"
        },
        "Reactions": []
      },
      "ThreadReplies": [],
      "id": "20260315-2-bbb03"
    },
    {
      "Channel": {
        "name": "arch-AnalyticsFlow",
        "channelID": "ch-aflw-ab1234"
      },
      "Message": {
        "User": {
          "userId": "eid_bc8960a9",
          "timestamp": "2026-03-15T14:18:00",
          "text": "I reviewed the API gateway section. We should consider rate limiting per tenant rather than global limits. This will be critical for our enterprise customers.",
          "utterranceID": "20260315-3-bbb04"
        },
        "Reactions": []
      },
      "ThreadReplies": [],
      "id": "20260315-3-bbb04"
    },
    {
      "Channel": {
        "name": "arch-AnalyticsFlow",
        "channelID": "ch-aflw-ab1234"
      },
      "Message": {
        "User": {
          "userId": "eid_6c031199",
          "timestamp": "2026-03-15T14:21:00",
          "text": "@eid_a3b1799d Nice work on the microservices decomposition. However, the event bus choice needs more justification - why Kafka over RabbitMQ for our use case?",
          "utterranceID": "20260315-4-bbb05"
        },
        "Reactions": []
      },
      "ThreadReplies": [],
      "id": "20260315-4-bbb05"
    },
    {
      "Channel": {
        "name": "arch-AnalyticsFlow",
        "channelID": "ch-aflw-ab1234"
      },
      "Message": {
        "User": {
          "userId": "eid_07a0ca6e",
          "timestamp": "2026-03-15T14:24:00",
          "text": "The security section looks comprehensive. One addition: we need to document the OAuth2 token rotation strategy, especially for long-running batch jobs.",
          "utterranceID": "20260315-5-bbb06"
        },
        "Reactions": []
      },
      "ThreadReplies": [],
      "id": "20260315-5-bbb06"
    },
