  "meeting_transcripts": [
    {
      "id": "mt_aflw_arch_review_001",
      "title": "AnalyticsFlow Architecture Review",
      "date": "2026-03-17T15:00:00",
      "participants": [
        "eid_a3b1799d",
        "eid_37f8a88b",
        "eid_8b8148f6",
        "eid_386ecbe0"
      ],
      "transcript": "\neid_a3b1799d: Let's go through the Technical Architecture Document for AnalyticsFlow. I want to address some of the feedback from the Slack discussion.\neid_37f8a88b: I've been reviewing the data pipeline section. The proposed batch processing window of 4 hours might be too long for real-time analytics use cases.\neid_8b8148f6: Agreed. We should also consider adding a streaming layer using Apache Flink. That would complement the Kafka setup nicely.\neid_386ecbe0: From the infrastructure side, the autoscaling policies need to account for the bursty nature of our analytics workloads. I'd recommend Kubernetes HPA with custom metrics.\neid_a3b1799d: Good points all around. Let me update the document with these considerations. We'll reconvene next week.\n"
    },
